citeinfo.title: 1:10,000 Vegetation, Niwot Ridge LTER Project Area, Colorado

pubinfo.publish: Niwot Ridge LTER, Institute of Arctic and Alpine Research (INSTAAR), University of Colorado

descript.abstract: Vegetation coverage digitized from 1:10,000 map. Vegetation classification follows Komarkova's (1979) classification system (Braun-Blanquet) units. See Peddle and Duguay (1995) for additional information on digitization and map production for this vegetation coverage. See Braun-Blanquet (1964), Komarkova and Webber (1978), and Komarkova (1979, 1980) for additional information on vegetation classification used in this dataset.
descript.purpose: A vegetation layer/coverage is necessary for some analyses on Niwot Ridge.
descript.supplinf:
This coverage generated was outside of the Tundra Ecosystem Analysis and Mapping Laboratory (TEAML) (both by students/workers for Claude Duguay in Canada). May have been compacted from the north somehow. Definitely some errors within.
Source map from Komarkova (1980); map digitized in spring of 1997.
Note, 2019-02-22: This dataset was made in the 1990s and has been minimally maintained since then (e.g. metadata may have been updated). While best reasonable effort has been made to quality check and describe this dataset, the data and metadata are provided largely as produced and described as they were when created.
This dataset has been converted from coverage to shapefile format for greater user accessibility. Shapefiles do not store topology and so topology from the coverage dataset was not transferred to the shapefile during conversion. If interested in data topology, please see the ArcInfo interchange file, veg.e00 (available in data package download), for the original coverage dataset with topology preserved. An .e00 file can be imported in ArcGIS Desktop applications via ArcToolbox tools: Conversion > To Coverage > Import from E00. It may also be read in to R via the 'readGDAL' function in R package 'rgdal'. Please note if import from .e00, the metadata displayed for the coverage will not be current.
Publications relevant to dataset: [1] Braun-Blanquet J. 1964. Pflanzensoziologie, Grundzüge der Vegetationskunde. 3 ed. Springer, Vienna and New York. 865 pp. [2] Komarkova V, Webber PJ. 1978. An Alpine Vegetation Map of Niwot Ridge, Colorado, Arctic and Alpine Research. 10:1-29. 10.1080/00040851.1978.12003941 [3] Komarkova V. 1979. Alpine vegetation of the Indian Peaks Area, Front Range, Colorado Rocky Mountains. In Tuxen, R. (editor), Flora et vegetatio mundi, VII. Vaduz: Cramer, 591 pp. [4] Komarkova V. 1980. Classification and ordination in the Indian Peaks area, Colorado Rocky Mountains. Vegetatio. 42(1/3): 149-163. [5] Peddle DR, Duguay C. 1995. Incorporating topographic and climatic GIS data into satellite image analysis of an alpine tundra ecosystem, front range, Colorado rocky mountains. Geocarto International. 10:43-60. 10.1080/10106049509354511

procstep.procdesc: Coverage imported from .e00 file, then converted to shapefile in ArcMap v10.5.[ATW, NWT PRA]

Coverage topology fields removed from shapefile attribute table, field names corrected, and .dbf written out in R using package 'foreign' v.0.8-70. Shapefile xml metadata edited for FGDC compliance and written out in R using package 'XML' v3.98-1.16.[CTW, NWT GRA]
